reviewText: funny dvd, thanks for the laugh.
a great and excellent cast great acting and singing a good and powerful play you really could relate to some of the issues a great play loved it
It don't with real family issues. Often times people like to sweep things under the rug in this play they dealt with the issues.
loved this movie. The acting and singing was very enjoyable. the story they were telling was very funny and a good musical.
What a wonderful message this play was! There was lots of laughter, love and a great message of forgiveness and love.
This was so hilarious, yet touching and poignant! I really think this is a must see for anyone at any age!
I thoroughly enjoyed the play, I only wish there were more plays from this family.  They are truly a talented group of God's children.

There is no way you can watch this play and be the same afterwards! You will laugh, be encouraged, and uplifted!  This is one of the best plays I have ever seen and I don't say that lightly.

Also these are all siblings! How cool is that?! :-)
Get it! You won't be disappointed! :-) Matter of fact...I'm going to watch again right now.

I must say that I really enjoyed the production, but what could I expect from the Sutton family other than mere perfection....  You all have been an awesome family since I met you all and God is still showing himself mighty through you all.

Now listen up viewers.... If you want a play that will tickle your funny plus minister to you.... This is the play here.... Watch and be blessed!!!

Be prepared to laugh, sing, shake your head and cry, but through it all know that life's hardships are nothing with family and an unwavering faith in the Lord to sustain you and hold you up! Awesome job Sutton Family!
